  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Number of participants with SIRS as assessed by SOFA-Score</measure>
    <time_frame>30 days</time_frame>
    <description>The study investigates the relationship between the intra-individual inflammatory patterns in patients with uncomplicated (no SIRS) and complicated postoperative courses (SIRS) after open heart surgery.
The diagnosis of SIRS will be made by using the Sepsis-related Organ Failure Assessment score (SOFA-score). Patients with an increase in SOFA-score &gt;3 are considered to have SIRS.</description>
